RPF periodically evaluates the performance of each contractor in fulfilling their obligations.  Contractors are obligated to perform the following:
1.  Assure that each contract employee is trained in the work practices necessary to safely perform his/her job;
2.  Assure that each contract employee is instructed in the known potential fire, explosion, or toxic release hazards related to his/her job and the process, and all applicable emergency response procedures;
3.  Document that each contract employee has received and understood the required training;
4.  Assure that each contract employee follows safety rules and safe work practices;
5.  Advise RPF of any unique hazards presented by the contractor's work or of any hazards found.

The plant implements an extensive written contractor PSM program that includes an orientation conducted by plant employees. Successful completion of the contractor orientation process results in contractor employees being issued a badge necessary to access the PSM covered processes. 

1.5   FIVE-YEAR ACCIDENT HISTORY

Rayonier Performance Fibers LLC Fernandina Plant keeps records for all significant accidental chemical releases which occur at the Fernandina Beach facility.  RMP defines accidental releases from covered process as those that resulted in (1) on-site deaths, injuries, or significant property damage, or (2) known off-site consequences such as death, injury, evacuation, sheltering in place, property damage, or environmental damage. 

